  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Financially sustaining organisation providing profitable agribusiness services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Chadiza District Farmers Association (CDFA) was formed in 1998 and the Association was officially registered on 9th May, 2005 with the Registrar of Societies under the laws of Zambia. There are 13 Board Members in the Association, among the Board Members.  The association decided to develop and submit a concept to United States Development of Africa &#x2013; USADF to process cooking oil from sunflower which they have been funded.This has helped them develop a business and are in cake and cooking oil business. This business has been running since 2015 and showing signs of financial independence from the side of the association.


The association has also acquired a tractor and light truck under the same USADF funding programme. This is meant to diversify the business and also increase income and sustainability of the association.
The desire by the association to diverse their income sources as a way of on increasing their capital base and reducing on donor dependency. The association also realizes the need to increase its membership base as it has an impact on their revenue, however the association sees the need to provide more membership services to its members as a way of proving its relevance need for members to affiliate.        

To diversify the tractor business and also increase income and sustainability of the association. A financially self-sustaining organisation providing quality services to 4,750 members towards a profitable agribusiness, by focusing on improved crop production, promoting mixed-farming and improved marketing of produce from their members. They also want to improve the sunflower business in terms of increased access to raw materials, production of quality raw materials and increase in quantities.</narrative>
  </description>
